        "label": "hanuman flying over sea",
        "text": "Hanuman detonates across the void between one island and the next, hurling himself off solid ground with an explosive, earth-shaking surge, while the sea below convulses and heaves, its surface tearing into violent white spray and drifting salt-thick mist that stings the air with pressure and brine.\n\nThe mid-air passage stretches like a suspended illusion above the restless ocean, where wind shears around his form in roaring spirals, and the water beneath draws in heavy, living currents that surge forward and recoil in rhythmic, relentless violence.\n\nHe drives forward into the rushing air as if floating within it, while the other locks around the gadha, his body slicing through layered light and shifting shadow as sky and sea collapse into one roaring field of motion beneath him."
