        "label": "krishna river side",
        "text": "A vibrant peacock feather spirals through the cool riverside wind in the extreme foreground, its delicate strands flexing and trembling as the camera glides inches beside its slow вращение-like drift, while blurred mountain ridges carve dark jagged silhouettes against the liquid gold-blue twilight shimmering across the restless river behind it. The camera begins a smooth circular orbit around the falling feather as soft gusts sweep flower petals and glowing particles through the air in layered currents, skimming low above the cold reflective water where faint ripples widen outward with quiet, glass-like tension beneath drifting bands of silver mist. As the rotation completes, Krishna gradually emerges from only side and back angles beside the riverbank, peacefully playing the flute strictly with his lips (flute should be very close to lips and not near chin) beneath the leaning tree while the wind threads through the hanging branches and flips clusters of leaves from deep green to pale silver in the fading light. The reflective water murmurs with slow-moving current beside Krishna, catching fractured streaks of amber and sapphire twilight that ripple and dissolve across its surface like living light beneath the breathing haze hovering above the shore. The camera slowly widens behind Krishna as the immense mountains loom in softened distance through layered twilight vapour, birds gliding silently across the vast sky while faint expanding ripples pulse through the mirror-like river under the cool drifting mist."
